Heat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Cook pasta as directed on package, omitting salt. Meanwhile, cook meat, onion, pepper, zucchini and taco seasoning mix in large skillet on medium-high heat until meat is evenly browned, stirring occasionally. Drain pasta. Add to meat mixture along with tomatoes; stir. Bring just to boil. Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese. Spoon into 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray. Bake 20 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake 3 to 5 minutes or until melted.